message_out: (1/23) A healthy crop makes a wealthy farmer. Follow Sala and Eli to learn to grow healthier, redder, sweeter tomatoes. Reply * to go back Reply A to continue
(2/23) Eli and Sala have 1 acre farms in Nyandarua. Last season Eli harvested small tomatoes. Sala's tomatoes were big and very red. Reply A to continue

(3/23) What caused Sala's tomatoes to grow big and red?
1. He used fertilizer that had special nutrients.
2. The soil on his farm was fertile.

Very good. Sala used Yara fertilizer that has special nutrients that made his tomatoes grow healthy, big and red.
Reply A to continue
(4/23) Both farmers bought fertilizer at the same trusted agrovet. Sala bought Yara fertilizer and Eli bought commercial fertilizer. Reply A to continue
(5/23) During transplanting, Eli used 50kgs of fertilizer on his farm while Sala used 50kgs of Yara Mila Unik 17 4 days after transplanting. Reply A to continue
(6/23) After transplanting, roots take 4 days to harden or get used to the new soil. Before hardening, they won't absorb fertilizer well. Reply A to continue
(7/23) Sala applied 30g of fertilizer to each seedling. He used a soda bottle top 3 times since 1 bottle top measures 10g. Reply A to continue

(8/23) Why is it important to apply Yara fertilizer 4 days after transplanting tomato seedlings?
1. To wait for rain
2. The roots absorb nutrients better.

Great! Tomato roots take 4 days to harden and are able to absorb nutrients better.
Reply A to continue
(9/23) Yara Mila Unik 17 has phosphorus, nitrogen and potassium which  help early crop establishment and vigorous growth. Reply A to continue
(10/23) When big leaves sprouted, Eli used 50kgs of commercial top dress while Sala used 100kgs of Yara Liva Nitrabor top dress. Reply * menu Reply A to continue
(11/23) Yara Liva Nitrabor has boron to harden the tomato skin, and calcium to make the crop resistant to disease like Blossom End Rot. Reply A to continue

(12/23) How many kgs of Yara Mila Unik should you apply for 2 acres and how much per seedling?
1. 50 kgs & 10g per seedling
2. 100kgs & 30g per seedling

Great! Not quite. Apply 50kgs per acre. So for 2 acres it is 100kgs of Yara Unik and 30g per seedling. Using less fertilizer reduces harvest.
Reply A to continue
(13/23) When the tomatoes started flowering, Eli didn't apply a second top dress. Sala applied 75kgs of Yara Mila Winner. Reply * for menu Reply A to continue
(1/23) A healthy crop makes a wealthy farmer. Follow Sala and Eli to learn to grow healthier, redder, sweeter tomatoes. Reply * to go back Reply A to continue
